cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

This paper deals with designing an SDN-style wide-area traffic scheduler for optimizing different completion time objectives for bulk transfers between datacenters. The paper focuses on network optimization and traffic scheduling, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also deals with datacenter communication and optimization, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper uses optimization techniques to minimize completion time objectives, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses simulation and emulation techniques to evaluate the proposed scheduler, which falls under the category of performance (cs.PF).
